### 1. Do you like reading?

Yes, I do enjoy reading, although I wouldn’t say I read on a daily basis. I usually read when I have some free time, especially in the evenings before going to bed. What I really like about reading is that it allows me to relax while also learning something new. In a way, it’s both entertaining and productive at the same time, which is why I’ve been trying to read more regularly.

👉 是的，我确实喜欢阅读，不过我不会每天都读。我通常在有空的时候读，尤其是在晚上睡前。我喜欢阅读的原因是它既能让我放松，又能让我学到新东西。从某种程度上说，它既有趣又有收获，这也是为什么我一直在尝试更规律地阅读。

---

### 2. What kind of books do you usually read?

I mainly read non-fiction books, especially those related to self-improvement and technology. As a computer science student, I’m quite interested in topics like artificial intelligence and productivity. I find these kinds of books not only informative but also practical, because I can actually apply what I learn to my studies or daily life. Occasionally, I also read novels, but not as often.

👉 我主要读非虚构类书籍，尤其是与自我提升和科技相关的内容。作为一名计算机专业学生，我对人工智能和效率提升这类话题很感兴趣。我觉得这类书不仅信息丰富，而且很实用，因为我可以把学到的东西应用到学习或生活中。偶尔我也会读小说，但不太频繁。

---

### 3. Do you prefer reading books or watching videos?

I’d say I generally prefer watching videos because they are more engaging and easier to understand, especially when the topic is complex. For example, if I’m learning something technical, videos can explain concepts more clearly with visuals. However, books tend to provide deeper insights and more detailed explanations. So in reality, I try to use both depending on what I want to achieve.

👉 我一般更喜欢看视频，因为它们更有吸引力，也更容易理解，尤其是在内容比较复杂的时候。比如在学习技术知识时，视频通过画面可以更清晰地解释概念。不过书籍通常提供更深入和更详细的内容。所以实际上我会根据目的来结合使用两者。

