# 🎤 Part 2（保持1.5分钟）

### Describe a book you found interesting

I’d like to talk about a book called Atomic Habits, which I read about a year ago.

👉 我想谈一本叫《Atomic Habits》的书，我大约在一年前读过。

This book focuses on how small habits can lead to significant improvements over time.

👉 这本书主要讲小习惯如何随着时间带来巨大的提升。

What I found particularly interesting is that the author explains complex ideas in a very simple and practical way.

👉 我觉得特别有意思的是，作者把复杂的概念讲得非常简单且实用。

For example, instead of encouraging people to set big goals, he suggests focusing on building small, consistent habits.

👉 比如，他并不鼓励设定宏大目标，而是建议建立小而持续的习惯。

This idea really changed the way I approach learning, especially when I’m studying programming or preparing for exams.

👉 这个观点改变了我学习的方式，尤其是在学编程或备考时。

Overall, I found the book extremely practical and inspiring, and I’ve actually applied many of its ideas in my daily life.

👉 总的来说，我觉得这本书非常实用且有启发性，而且我已经把很多理念用在日常生活中了。

